Swedish music producer and DJ, Avicii has been found dead in Oman, a Middle Eastern country at the age of 28. The DJ, whose real name is Tim Bergling, was found dead on Friday afternoon in Oman. “It is with profound sorrow that we announce the loss of Tim Bergling, also known as Avicii. He was found dead in Muscat, Oman. The family is devastated and we ask everyone to please respect their need for privacy in this difficult time. No further statements will be given,” his representatives told the international media. Avicii was known to have struggled with several health issues including acute pancreatitis which was allegedly due to excessive drinking. He also had his gallbladder and appendix removed in 2014. He is best known for songs such as Wake Me Up and Levels. The international entertainment community is expressing their shock and sadness at the loss of a musical genius. 